description.en:
Individual or group in-class presentation of a country case study (15 mins)

Assessment criteria:
- show knowledge of the current situation in the country/region;
- present position and opinions;
- apply theoretical arguments to an empirical case;
- submission of a 1-page memo in advance of the class;
- able to stick to the time limit.

The students should be able to show their knowledge of the developing situation in the country/region; present their thoughts and opinions on the topics; and apply the theoretical literature discussed in class to the selected country case. The memo should be succinct and summarise the most relevant aspects of the country case. Further instructions will be provided via Moodle in due course.

The presentation will either be individual or group (most likely 2 people), depending on how many students sign up for the course. We will decide this by the end of February, the presentations will be held in May.

